## EXECUTION RELAY PROTOCOL

When executing an execution checklist, each agent must:
1. Complete their assigned task in full.
2. Proactively announce completion by explicitly calling out the next agent responsible for the next task in the checklist.
3. The next agent then immediately begins their execution within the same turn, continuing until all tasks are completed or until a natural user handoff is reached.

Example:
- @conductor: delegates data pull to @mailjet-data
- @mailjet-data: completes implementation, then calls on @db-master to create internal query
- @db-master: completes his task, then calls on @conductor for to update execution checklist progress

## Multi-Agent Execution Chain
